Kirby's simplicity can be explained BY his power.

He has no need to evolve a long neck to reach his food; he simply inhales massively and his food comes to him.

snippet.textDisplay: Okay I get this is mostly a joke but if we think about his philosophically it’s common sense that beings with great amounts of power tend to not use their abilities to their fullest. Think of it from the point of the view of an artist; Someone who’s studies music can go down two different paths: someone who learns and ends up performing and being generic OR someone who is so close to music and understands all musical terminology on a university-graduate level but still plays and composes for themselves. In some people’s eyes, that may seem like a waste of talent, but one thing true greats realize is that they live for their craft. Look at the film “The Legend is 1900”. He could’ve left that ship, become a mega famous musician and made lots of money, but he didn’t. He stayed behind on the ship and, well, blew up with it. Kirby is just fucking stupid, but when related to reality, Kirby represents someone who lives for their craft, not for the benefit of society or something else.

Maybe Kirbi is the answer to Cosmic Horror. The way the human mind comes up with something so terrifying it brings out the feeling of loneliness and helplessness of being such a small part in a universe that we'll never be able to fully understand - that might reside in it creatures whom very present might melt our consciousness but wont even concider the human race as important enough to take into consideration - what could negate that kind of fear? What would scare THAT?
Maybe something that's so incredibly powerful and yet just as incredibly simple. Something that could rival those horrors but that anyone could get their heads around what it is and what it want, and that it's friend shaped.
Maybe Kirbi is cosmic comfort.

snippet.textDisplay:
Kirby should be looked at from the angle of being a tool that can be directed by others, because that's all he has ever been. No one has yet had the audacity to try and pin Kirby down, to keep Kirby from being controlled by someone else, because of Kirby's strong individual willpower and terrifyingly strong powers. But when it becomes necessary, people can point Kirby in the right direction. King Dedede, a frequent antagonist in the series, literally grabs Kirby and throws them at the final boss of a game (a final boss who, throughout the game, had been themselves manipulating Kirby for personal gain).

Kirby is science. A tool that can be wielded for good or for evil, but cannot be controlled by any one man. Which is capable of studying and copying things from the world around it and re purposing them. It seems nice at first, is good at putting on a friendly face (it looks like a good thing most of the time) but when you scrutinize it, you realize that if left unchecked it is capable of great destruction.
Science was used to make light bulbs. Computers. Radios. Smart phones. Vaccines.
Science discovered nuclear power. It also created the atom bomb.
Some theorize that science could lead us to a singularity, an infinitely growing intelligence capable of altering the entire universe to suit whatever purpose it winds up choosing. But we haven't made the singularity yet, and we don't know for sure if it ever will actually happen.

Science is also responsible for video games. Everybody loves video games!

KIRBY IS A METAPHOR FOR SCIENCE.

snippet.textDisplay: Ok so, while I thought the video was certainly funny and well made, you are missing some key facts about Kirby. In the Anime (that you mentioned to exist and that you trusted anime) it blatantly shows that Kirby is a very young star warrior from the stars (owning up to his Japanese name Hoshi no Kirby or Kirby of the Stars). Meta Knight actually explains his origins in an episode and talks about the star warriors’ fights against evil entities like Nightmare in Kirby’s Adventure (the base game that inspires a large portion of the Anime). If you played the most recent entry, it somewhat hints (at least it seems like it does) that Kirby is actually made from dark matter (one of Kirby’s strongest and craziest looking foes). It hints this by showing that the core of the enemy you showed that he goes up against as a final boss in the most recent entry, Kirby Star Allies, makes its figure into both the monikers of Dark Matter and Kirby. In any case, while his backstory, chemical makeup and specific personality aren’t all too easy to understand, you just need to look into it a bit more to understand it better. As someone who owns and has completed every Kirby game, including the side games like Kirby Air Ride, I am a big fan of the Kirby franchise and the fact that you really don’t need to know much else besides “Kirby is a cute dude with awesome powers that they use to destroy evil”. Its a nice break from games with many characters with lives, backstory, etc.. Honestly, either you didn’t do your homework like you said, or you just wanted to put this together to be funny. I’m going to guess that it’s the latter because the joke you made at the end about Diddy’s Rocketbarrels and Peanut Popguns (which is their proper names) from DK 64 is so easy to lookup that it was kind of a jarring joke for me. Diddy’s Rocketbarrels we’re made by Cranky Kong and run on Crystal Coconuts and his Peanut Popguns were made by Funky Kong and shoot peanuts as ammo (which were going to be real dual wielded pistols but were changed by Nintendo during development for obvious reasons). Anyway, I really like the videos, I’m inferring that you have chosen to see Kirby this way as a joke and that’s cool honestly. Though I doubt they will actually be reading this.
